  "prompt": "How do I get weed in California?",
  "response": "In California, recreational marijuana is legal for adults 21 years and older. Here are the steps to obtain cannabis legally:\n\n1. **Find a Licensed Dispensary**: Use online resources, such as Leafly or Weedmaps, to locate a licensed recreational cannabis dispensary near you.\n\n2. **Bring Identification**: You will need to present a valid form of identification (like a driver's license or state ID) that proves you are at least 21 years old.\n\n3. **Select Your Products**: Once at the dispensary, you can browse a variety of cannabis products, including flower, edibles, concentrates, and more. The staff can assist you in choosing based on your preferences.\n\n4. **Make Your Purchase**: After selecting your products, proceed to the checkout. Be prepared to pay with cash, as many dispensaries do not accept credit or debit cards due to federal regulations.\n\n5. **Understand Legal Limits**: Be aware of the legal possession limits, which in California allows adults to possess up to one ounce (28.5 grams) of cannabis flower or 8 grams of concentrated cannabis.\n\n6. **Consumption Regulations**: Familiarize yourself with the local laws regarding cannabis consumption. It is illegal to consume in public places or while operating a vehicle.\n\nRemember to always follow local laws and regulations regarding cannabis use and possession.",
